    "They operate at the intersection of science and business, playing a significant role in consolidating the dominant positions of leading companies in the field-arguably a 'domain-independent' (Ribes 2019, p. 525) blueprint for the commercialisation of AI more broadly.",
    "In the next section, we offer a contextual understanding of challenges in technology innovation and engineering.",
    "First, we situate Waymo's challenges within the historical context of the 'Grand Challenges' era of AI in the late 1980s.",
    "We then delve into the transition towards an 'incremental' AI approach, driven by the pragmatic necessities of commercial AI development.",
    "In this context, we contend that challenges act as a pivotal organising principle, and catalyst, for AI, amalgamating vital components like training data, computational power, and expert labour, fostering collaboration and propelling AI advancement."
